0w, https://static.digit.in/3-10.png 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"204\" height=\"115\"></figure><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:311/175;\" src=\"https://static.digit.in/4-13-1024x576.png\" alt=\"ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/4-13-1024x576.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-300x169.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-768x432.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-1536x864.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-2048x1152.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-267x150.png 267w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-100x56.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-622x350.png 622w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-788x443.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-599x337.png 599w, https://static.digit.in/4-13-150x84.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/4-13.png 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"311\" height=\"175\"></figure><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:311/175;\" src=\"https://static.digit.in/5-10-1024x576.png\" alt=\"ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/5-10-1024x576.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-300x169.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-768x432.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-1536x864.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-2048x1152.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-267x150.png 267w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-100x56.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-622x350.png 622w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-788x443.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-599x337.png 599w, https://static.digit.in/5-10-150x84.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/5-10.png 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"311\" height=\"175\"></figure><p>Of course, the laptop also comes with a 14th gen Intel processor, and while we do have Ultra processors in the market, we’re still waiting on Ultra processor gaming laptops. We compared the Intel Core i9-14900HX in the ROG Strix SCAR 16 to the Intel Core i9-13980HX in the MSI Raider GE78 HX just to see how much of a difference in performance there is between the two.</p><p><a href=\"https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity.png\"><img src=\"https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-1024x634.png\" alt=\"ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-1024x634.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-300x186.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-768x475.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-1536x950.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-2048x1267.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-242x150.png 242w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-100x62.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-566x350.png 566w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-788x487.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-600x371.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity-150x93.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/Processor-and-Productivity.png 1348w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"634\"></a></p><p>Turns out, not a lot. The difference is almost negligible in most scores with the newer 14th gen processor inching slightly ahead in single-core performance.</p><p>And that’s not even the best part. There’s barely any thermal throttling, thanks to ASUS’s Intelligent Cooling technology.</p><p>No seriously, this thing runs <i>cool</i>. Even after hours of gaming. Recording heat at our usual spots, we saw peak surface temps of just 38 degrees Celsius with the average surface temp rounding out to around 25 degrees. The only laptop that scored higher than the SCAR 16 on thermal throttling is the SCAR 18, but even that had higher surface temps than the SCAR 16.</p><h2><strong>Display</strong></h2><p>The display is easily one of the best things the SCAR 16 has going for it. The 16-inch Quad HD+ (2560x1600p) ROG Nebula HDR display comes with a refresh rate of 240Hz. It’s got vibrant colours, inky blacks, and buttery smooth visuals. The mini LEDs enable better local dimming, and with 100% sRGB and DCI-P3 colour gamut coverage, plus Dolby Vision compliance, this is one of the best gaming displays you can find on a gaming laptop.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://static.digit.in/h732.png\"><img src=\"https://static.digit.in/h732-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/h732-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/h732-300x300.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/h732-150x150.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/h732-768x768.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/h732-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/h732-2048x2048.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/h732-100x100.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/h732-350x350.png 350w, https://static.digit.in/h732-788x788.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/h732-600x600.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/h732-96x96.png 96w, https://static.digit.in/h732.png 732w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\"></a></p><h2><strong>ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16 Build &amp; Design</strong></h2><p>Moving on to the design, the Scar 16 screams gamer, but not in a tacky way. The aluminium and plastic construction makes it sturdy with close to zero flex. The RGB LED strips surrounding the rear and side vents light up the Scar in striking colours using the Aura Sync software. However, it isn’t the most portable laptop at almost 3 kg.</p><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:632/632;\" src=\"https://static.digit.in/6-11-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/6-11-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-300x300.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-150x150.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-768x768.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-2048x2048.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-100x100.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-350x350.png 350w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-788x788.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-600x600.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/6-11-96x96.png 96w, https://static.digit.in/6-11.png 732w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"632\" height=\"632\"></figure><h2><strong>Ports</strong></h2><p>Connectivity-wise, the Scar 16 does not disappoint. With two USB-A and two USB-C ports (including one Thunderbolt 4), HDMI, audio, and Gigabit Ethernet ports, it’s got you covered. No storage card reader though, but this laptop is all about power.</p><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:311/311;\" src=\"https://static.digit.in/3-11-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/3-11-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-300x300.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-150x150.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-768x768.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-2048x2048.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-100x100.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-350x350.png 350w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-788x788.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-600x600.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/3-11-96x96.png 96w, https://static.digit.in/3-11.png 732w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"311\" height=\"311\"></figure><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:311/311;\" src=\"https://static.digit.in/2-16-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/2-16-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-300x300.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-150x150.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-768x768.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-2048x2048.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-100x100.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-350x350.png 350w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-788x788.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-600x600.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/2-16-96x96.png 96w, https://static.digit.in/2-16.png 732w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"311\" height=\"311\"></figure><h2><strong>Keypad and Touchpad</strong></h2><p>The keyboard offers a satisfying experience with a crisp, tactile bottoming action. It’s not mechanical, but it’s quick and comfortable, ideal for gaming. The touchpad is spacious, providing a responsive tracking experience. Gamers will likely opt for a dedicated mouse, and in a pinch, the touchpad also doubles as a Numpad, which adds a neat touch.</p><p><a href=\"https://static.digit.in/5-12.png\"><img src=\"https://static.digit.in/5-12-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16\" srcset=\"https://static.digit.in/5-12-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-300x300.png 300w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-150x150.png 150w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-768x768.png 768w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-2048x2048.png 2048w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-100x100.png 100w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-350x350.png 350w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-788x788.png 788w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-600x600.png 600w, https://static.digit.in/5-12-96x96.png 96w, https://static.digit.in/5-12.png 732w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\"></a></p><h2><strong>ASUS ROG Strix SCAR 16 Verdict</strong></h2><p>In conclusion, the ASUS ROG Strix Scar 16 is a game-changer, delivering desktop-level performance in a 16-inch laptop form factor. It’s a powerhouse that keeps up with the Scar legacy, featuring the most potent hardware in a premium chassis with a jaw-dropping display. While the range starts at ₹2,89,990, the variant we reviewed comes in at ₹3,29,990. If you’re serious about gaming and want a show-stopping experience, the SCAR 16 is worth every penny.</p>', 1, '2024-03-04 00:35:33', '2024-03-04 00:35:33');
